<article class="entry">

  <div class="entry-hero title-position-bottom" data-title="Corpse lay on the street in coronavirus-racked Rio for 30 hours">
    <span class="loader"></span>
    <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/OvarGu3Belsyxnll5FhK9w_QqUCf6LfQr8xsK2_XP_SYS78K_2BSqaySDRqAqRic8g5NK2DUgxu_oAGmAMEgWv1hykG6-W8mlWRVGeiq6HM4JY91iSUdsagQ1RSMsgeU 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/WBTnOVC7qqta06gXHeKsQxWuNywwiYpdn8d0Aw_rBjGaDSNXdIiJzt2uIcpaef_GT37oh75p6MDJqtI4qb6_CjsGEseeWv5Dzg5esupv-D98E5aBA-QVaXU6_3C4UJOA 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/Q_R5ChVKlRml3tKGh9ARANyV_u8RBRkFq9ovP_PjMeBryQ4XOXRNywGoFVuAejkCvUKrJTl_TmRUJj6L-2UygI2jYtLj7P4tg1z7tA5pITxFeA4XsJmb4GD7ojHsk6ZL 1230w" alt="Corpse lay on the street in coronavirus-racked Rio for 30 hours" />
  </div>

  <header class="entry-header">
    <h1 class="entry-title" itemprop="name headline">Corpse lay on the street in coronavirus-racked Rio for 30 hours</h1>

    <div class="entry-meta">
      <div class="entry-meta-top">
        <span class="location entry-location">
          <a class="location-icon" href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=-22.275276,-42.419415" target="_blank"></a>           Rio De Janeiro, <a href="/country/brazil">Brazil</a>
        </span>

          
      <span class="entry-large-author-list">
      <span class="entry-authors">
        <span>Photography by</span>
                                        
            <span class="entry-author" itemscope itemprop="author" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
              <span class="entry-author-name" itemprop="name">Ricardo Moraes</span>.            </span>
                  
      </span>

      <span class="entry-authors">
        <span>Reporting by</span>
                            <span class="entry-author" itemscope itemprop="author" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
            <span class="entry-author-name" itemprop="name">Gabriel Stargardter</span>.          </span>
        
      </span>
    </span>
  
    



      </div>

      <div class="entry-meta-bot">
        <time class="entry-date">Updated Tuesday</time>
        <span class="entry-imagesnumber">5 images</span>

        
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="entry-content">

    <div class="entry-ad">
      <span>Advertisement</span>
      <div class="entry-ad-wrapper">
          <div id="ad-story-leaderboard"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

          <p class="wrap">Valnir da Silva died on the streets of a poor Rio de Janeiro neighborhood on Saturday. His body lay on the sidewalk for 30 hours, according to relatives and neighbors.</p>
          <p class="wrap">Although they may never be sure, they suspect the 62-year-old was an uncounted victim of the coronavirus outbreak tearing through Rio&#039;s marginalized communities and stretching public services past their limits.</p>
    

                  <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DdHiQbw_buSWgB6em6EqBABZwOlilnS-PuynAl0az7eAnRZoPwSAS63pxzzylwEZ4Q 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSr2T8ZzgXX-J-FJpEk1vqY5RT5F730ZW-n4VtQtqMjHkKFtifv0xgvRn8stcR4ViLg 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6qW3wO1JyXK9NndN1Feh28QfBCQNP9GaZzioBjFG_H7GOqCVXTu6GuNa99dYOeAJRA 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>17 May 2020</time>. Rio De Janeiro, Brazil. Reuters/Ricardo Moraes
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
      <div class="image-caption">
      A funeral parlour worker stands next to police officers in the Acara slum.
    </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
                    <p>As much of Asia and Europe pass the worst of the pandemic, Brazil is hurtling toward its peak, with more than 17,000 already dead. Latin America&#039;s biggest country passed Britain this week in a grim toll of the most confirmed cases after Russia and the United States.</p>
              <p>Deaths in Rio state trail only the more populous Sao Paulo. The outbreak is filling up intensive care units and thinning out the ranks of emergency services.</p>
              <p>Ricardo Moraes, a Reuters photojournalist in Rio, was covering a police operation early on Sunday when he heard reports about the corpse in the nearby favela of Arara.</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                        <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DRGloa1ZMSC4qkQ6aAfEtRosqUWUMSABxcaTkQMYvl5mDsKa28WbZ70lqyJvKovdXQ 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSq-F216X_XyVTJ2qmvbrXwniu02r89PSN0QzTIIQS9mXLVKXf-QKzh05_e1agYPb9w 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6t-tXpW3r2vjAfNJ8nWO34n48iZ4DWU80K1zwBGtZodkJzsMZZffHc6h9-7S2e_V7g 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>17 May 2020</time>. Rio De Janeiro, Brazil. Reuters/Ricardo Moraes
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
      <div class="image-caption">
      Funeral parlour workers place Valnir Mendes da Silva&#039;s body into a casket.
    </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
                    <p>When he arrived at the scene around 7 a.m. on Sunday, Moraes found Silva lying on the same spot where locals said he had died on Saturday morning - sandwiched between a row of parked cars and a small soccer pitch.</p>
              <p>A group of locals at a nearby bar said Silva&#039;s life began to fall apart after the death of his wife a few months back, and he was soon living on the street.</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                        <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DV1kATdaUliDlO-MTY-SracqArDxC_TVvMqwYyX31O6oaAwhSEGRjTpwZDHtScqbDA 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSr42bZvzvd5eKA64p0QNZRGIRWWnICRTaSPPoZLGCsuNVeugVEKZnNGSsW7IV8m1hA 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6t2lfGkLoz0yGXQf7IOf3vA-umtyM7qLJ8uTrnmQn96VUiiuG-LHBEG9UgSxfvWr0A 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>17 May 2020</time>. Rio De Janeiro, Brazil. Reuters/Ricardo Moraes
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
      <div class="image-caption">
      Workers of a funeral parlour lean on a car after removing the body.
    </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
                    <p>On Saturday, when Silva complained that he could not breathe, the locals said they called an ambulance for him, but he died before it arrived.</p>
              <p>Some residents thought he had died from COVID-19, the respiratory diseases caused by the coronavirus, but nobody was certain. The disease entered Rio via wealthier residents returning from vacation in Europe, but it has since spread into poorer neighborhoods.</p>
              <p>The ambulance arrived around 4 p.m. on Saturday, locals said, but left without the body. Paramedics put his cause of death as cardiac arrest and another unknown cause, according to the death certificate seen by Reuters.</p>
              <p>In a statement, the city ambulance service said it was not responsible for removing the corpse. They did not say whether Silva had been tested for COVID-19.</p>
      
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                        <figure class="widget widget-image widget-image-large-center">
  <div class="image-wrapper">
          <img sizes="(min-width: 500px) 100vw, 50vw" srcset="https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/dqXP9WC0Q5E0WCSnUdU6DXhUeOMWDYs2SCAEgpsKYfEvO9Q3FnVQK0nmYDcuM4kCxP-cQCpM_Jvf0etFdh9UuA 480w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/JriyrsiwoBOmJqrlYRQaSu27mA5RtxcUfZB0__O4eKAlvyG5b83MAFkUfRTCAHfH-7e654NGNTa7roFW5r1lhg 768w, https://photos.wi.gcs.trstatic.net/e9hyHkaRFZdDV_jLZuTS6hQW5zfoJRMueEzrxBgZ_nElIuhxhvOT7F5o2qxzO8m5iYDklR9y7X7NmDkgtH9ijw 1230w" alt="" />
                <figcaption class="figure-meta">
      <time>18 May 2020</time>. Rio De Janeiro, Brazil. Reuters/Ricardo Moraes
    </figcaption>
    <span class="image-info"></span>
  </div>
      <div class="image-caption">
      Marcos Vinicius Andrade da Silva, 26, helps to carry the coffin of Valnir Mendes da Silva during his funeral at Cemiterio de Inhauma, a cemetery in Inhauma.
    </div>
    <div class="widget-content">
    <div class="wrap">
            
    </div>
  </div>
</figure>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
                
      
      
      
      
              <div class="wrap">
  <h3 class="is-hidden">Story</h3>
  
      
<p>The next morning, Silva's stepson Marcos Vinicius Andrade da Silva, 26, tried to find another authority to pick up the body.</p><p>    </p><p>He said he spoke with police officers on patrol, who alerted colleagues at the 21st Civil Police station nearby, to no avail.</p><p>    </p><p>A civil police spokeswoman said they only take charge of removing corpses in criminal cases.</p><p>    </p><p>After spending the day on the phone, the stepson said a funeral team arrived finally at 5 p.m. on Sunday.</p><p>    </p><p>"We were very relieved that they had taken him away... but also very sad about what happened," he said.</p><p>    </p><p>On Monday, da Silva was buried at a ceremony with four people, including Marcos and his mother, in attendance.</p>
  
      <p class="story-meta">
            PHOTO EDITING MARIKA KOCHIASHVILI; Text Editing Brad Haynes, Rosalba O&#039;Brien, LAYOUT JULIA DALRYMPLE
    </p>
  </div>

      
      
      
      
      
      
          

